---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About Calgary CX" description="Calgary CX is an independent thought leadership publication focused on CX, CCaaS, AI Agents, and Customer Service Operations.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>Calgary CX</h1>
      <p class="lead" style="max-width:600px;">Independent insights on CX, CCaaS, AI Agents, and Customer Service Operations. Based in Calgary, writing for the North American enterprise market.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <section>
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What This Is</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX is an independent publication covering the enterprise customer experience landscape. It exists because the dominant voices in the CCaaS and CX AI space are either vendor-aligned analysts, sponsored content platforms, or conference ecosystems with commercial incentives that don't always align with honest analysis.</p>
        <p>The content here is written from the perspective of a practitioner — someone who has actually worked through CCaaS migrations, structured UAT programmes, evaluated AI vendors, and operated managed services relationships for large enterprise clients.</p>
        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>CCaaS</strong> — Cloud contact center platforms, migrations, and vendor evaluations across Genesys Cloud, NICE CXone Mpower, Amazon Connect, and others.</li>
          <li><strong>CX AI</strong> — Artificial intelligence applied to customer experience, including evaluation frameworks and governance considerations.</li>
          <li><strong>AI Agents</strong> — Autonomous voice and digital agents and how to deploy them responsibly.</li>
          <li><strong>Workforce Optimization</strong> — WFM, quality management, interaction analytics, and the shifting role of AI in agent performance.</li>
          <li><strong>CX Strategy</strong> — Operating model design, QBR structures, and strategic decisions facing CX leaders.</li>
          <li><strong>Operations</strong> — The practical, daily reality of running contact center operations at scale.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
        <p>Calgary CX is not sponsored by any vendor, platform, or service provider. When specific vendors or products are referenced, it is because they are relevant to the topic — not because of any commercial arrangement. See our <a href="/disclaimer">full disclaimer</a>.</p>
        <h2>The Calgary Angle</h2>
        <p>Calgary is home to a significant cluster of enterprise organizations across energy, financial services, retail, and telecommunications. The Canadian context matters: PIPEDA compliance, bilingualism requirements, and the pragmatic operational culture of Western Canadian enterprise all shape how these decisions play out. We write from that context.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div style="background:var(--mist);padding:4rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Start Reading</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--text-3);margin-bottom:2rem;">Explore our latest articles and videos on enterprise CX.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <a href="/articles" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Articles</a>
        <a href="/videos" class="btn btn-outline">Watch Videos</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
